aa(lp180
VSo, what do we need to know
p181
aVin order to predict?
p182
aVYou may be surprised to find out we don't need to know very much.
p183
aVWe do need to know who has a stake
p184
aVin trying to shape the outcome of a decision.
p185
aVWe need to know what they say they want,
p186
aVnot what they want in their heart of hearts,
p187
aVnot what they think they can get,
p188
aVbut what they say they want, because that is a strategically chosen position,
p189
aVand we can work backwards from that
p190
aVto draw inferences about important features of their decision-making.
p191
aVWe need to know how focused they are
p192
aVon the problem at hand.
p193
aVThat is, how willing are they to drop what they're doing when the issue comes up,
p194
aVand attend to it instead of something else that's on their plate \u2014
p195
aVhow big a deal is it to them?
p196
aVAnd how much clout could they bring to bear
p197
aVif they chose to engage on the issue?
