aa(lp199
VIf we know those things
p200
aVwe can predict their behavior by assuming that everybody
p201
aVcares about two things on any decision.
p202
aVThey care about the outcome. They'd like an outcome as close to
p203
aVwhat they are interested in as possible.
p204
aVThey're careerists, they also care about getting credit \u2014
p205
aVthere's ego involvement,
p206
aVthey want to be seen as important in shaping the outcome,
p207
aVor as important, if it's their druthers, to block an outcome.
p208
aVAnd so we have to figure out how they balance those two things.
p209
aVDifferent people trade off
p210
aVbetween standing by their outcome,
p211
aVfaithfully holding to it, going down in a blaze of glory,
p212
aVor giving it up, putting their finger in the wind,
p213
aVand doing whatever they think is going to be a winning position.
p214
aVMost people fall in between, and if we can work out where they fall
p215
aVwe can work out how to negotiate with them
p216
aVto change their behavior.
